Alabama Department of Human Resources has concluded that the 88-year-old author is in a fit state to publish Go Set a Watchman  . 
  Lee lives in a nursing home in Monroeville and has been deaf and blind since 2007 . 
  Two investigations were launched into whether she was manipulated into publishing the sequel to To Kill a Mockingbird . 
  State officials say she is not an elder abuse victim . 
  Lee wrote the novel before To Kill A Mocking Bird and has said she wanted it to be her only published book . 
 